## Context
Reviewer 1 §4: loss-and-damage finance (Warsaw 2013, Santiago 2022, L&D Fund
2023) rests on an actuarial/insurance logic — compensation for prospective risk,
a liability regime — that does NOT fit the crystallisation-era categories
(incremental-cost / mobilisation). This challenges the thesis that post-2015
disputes stay "within established categories." Cannot be ignored for a paper
covering climate finance through 2024.

## Actions
1. Add a subsection acknowledging L&D/insurance as a genuinely different logic and a partial limit to the "disputes-within-established-categories" claim.
2. Note the game-theoretic / coalition-formation opening (insurance vs burden-sharing imply different coalition structures) — briefly, linking to §1.3.

## Exit criteria
- [ ] L&D/insurance logic addressed as a challenge, not absorbed silently
